         <abstract>
            <p>
               An algorithm is described for numerically evaluating functions defined by formal(and possibly divergent) series as well as convergent series of orthogonal functions which are, apart from a factor, orthogonal polynomials. When the orthogonal functions are polynomials, the approximations are rational functions. The algorithm is similar in some respects to the method of Padé approximants. A rational approximation involving Tchebychev polynomials due to H. Maehley and described by E. Kogbetliantz [1] is a special case of the algorithm. 
            </p>
          </abstract>
